<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
		Export Compliance declaration.

		Lattice VPN uses non-iOS-builtin encryption (WireGuard via
		WireGuardKitGo, Rosenpass via the bundled FFI). The original Cloak
		VPN-era submission set ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption=true here and
		paired it with an ECCN 5D992.c self-classification letter uploaded
		to App Store Connect, which generated a server-side compliance
		code that was matched against ITSEncryptionExportComplianceCode in
		this Info.plist. After the rebrand, that code stopped matching and
		blocked uploads ("Invalid Export Compliance Code").

		The simplest recovery path is to OMIT both the
		ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption key AND the matching
		ITSEncryptionExportComplianceCode from Info.plist entirely. Apple
		then prompts the encryption questionnaire on the version page of
		App Store Connect after upload — answer YES to non-exempt
		encryption, YES to qualifying for the mass-market exemption under
		ECCN 5D992.c, and the previously-uploaded self-classification PDF
		(docs/legal/CloakVPN-Encryption-Compliance.pdf) remains the
		supporting documentation on file.

		Once Apple approves the rebrand, regenerate compliance docs under
		the Lattice name and re-introduce the keys here for friction-free
		future uploads.
	-->

	<!--
		Bootstrap key for /api/v1/auth/exchange. Loaded at build time
		from Secrets.xcconfig (gitignored — never committed). Read at
		runtime via Bundle.main.infoDictionary["CLOAK_BOOTSTRAP_KEY"].
		Server-side counterpart is /etc/cloak/bootstrap-key on every
		region. To rotate:
		  1. openssl rand -base64 32 > new-bootstrap-key
		  2. scp to /etc/cloak/bootstrap-key on all 4 regions
		  3. systemctl restart cloak-api-server on each
		  4. Update CLOAK_BOOTSTRAP_KEY in clients/ios/CloakVPN/Secrets.xcconfig
		  5. Build + ship new TestFlight / App Store version
	-->
	<key>CLOAK_BOOTSTRAP_KEY</key>
	<string>$(CLOAK_BOOTSTRAP_KEY)</string>

	<!--
		User-facing display name on the home screen. Project / target /
		bundle ID still carry the historical "CloakVPN" identifier (those
		are Phase B once Apple approves), but the springboard label and
		every iOS system-generated VPN dialog show this string instead.
		"Lattice VPN" is the rebrand chosen after the 4.1(a) Copycats
		rejection — see docs/app-store/lattice-rebrand.md.
	-->
	<key>CFBundleDisplayName</key>
	<string>Lattice VPN</string>

	<!--
		Alternate app icons. The primary icon (LATTICE VPN lattice-shield
		logo) lives in Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset and is what the
		app shows by default. The "Pro" variant is registered here as a
		CFBundleAlternateIcons entry so we can switch to it at runtime via
		UIApplication.setAlternateIconName("LatticeProIcon") when the user
		upgrades their subscription.

		File-naming convention: iOS auto-resolves @2x and @3x suffixes,
		so we ship LatticeProIcon.png / @2x / @3x as loose PNGs in the
		bundle (NOT in the asset catalog — Apple's required pattern
		for alternate icons since iOS 11).

		UIPrerenderedIcon=true: the source PNGs already have the dark
		navy background baked in; we don't want iOS to apply its
		default gloss-overlay on top of them.
	-->
	<key>CFBundleIcons</key>
	<dict>
		<key>CFBundleAlternateIcons</key>
		<dict>
			<key>LatticeProIcon</key>
			<dict>
				<key>CFBundleIconFiles</key>
				<array>
					<string>LatticeProIcon</string>
				</array>
				<key>UIPrerenderedIcon</key>
				<true/>
			</dict>
		</dict>
	</dict>

	<!--
		(Historical) — App Transport Security exceptions for plain-HTTP
		region endpoints lived here until commit landing #19's HTTPS
		switch. Region URLs are now https://cloak-{region}.cloakvpn.ai
		on Let's Encrypt certs (auto-renewed via certbot.timer). iOS
		default ATS rules accept these without any exceptions. Removing
		the workaround eliminates a known App Store review rejection
		vector (reviewers flag NSExceptionDomains and ask for written
		justification).
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
